  <description type="morphology">Plants mostly erect, 1–3.5 × 1–5 dm. Aerial flowering stems erect or nearly so, scapelike or dichotomous, (0.7–)1–2.5 dm, tomentose to floccose. Leaves: blade linear to narrowly oblanceolate, (1.5–)3–9(–12) × 0.1–0.5(–0.7) cm, tomentose abaxially, less so and grayish or occasionally greenish adaxially, margins plane or more often revolute. Inflorescences umbellate or cymose divided 1–3 times and 2–5(–8) cm, or capitate and 1–2 cm; branches tomentose to floccose. Involucres 1 per node or more commonly 3–7 per cluster, turbinate to turbinate-campanulate, (2–)2.5–4 × 1.5–3 mm, usually tomentose, occasionally thinly floccose or glabrous. Flowers (2–)3–3.5(–4) mm; perianth yellow or ochroleucous, glabrous.</description>
